\ Parallel map: pmap (shortcut, num-cores workers / claim 1) and
\ pmap-ext ( array worker_count items_per_claim xt -- image ).
\ Every result is checked against the sequential `map` so the golden
\ output is independent of core count and worker scheduling.

\ pmap == map, basic
[ 1 2 3 4 5 ] dup [: 10 * :] map swap [: 10 * :] pmap = . cr

\ pmap-ext == map, explicit worker_count and items_per_claim
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 ] dup [: 1 + :] map swap 4 2 [: 1 + :] pmap-ext = . cr

\ order preserved in the image
[ 1 2 3 4 ] [: dup * :] pmap . cr

\ empty domain
[ ] [: 1 + :] pmap . cr

\ single element
[ 7 ] [: 1 + :] pmap . cr

\ worker_count clamped to domain length
[ 1 2 3 ] 99 1 [: 1 + :] pmap-ext . cr

\ items_per_claim larger than the whole domain
[ 1 2 3 ] 2 999 [: 1 + :] pmap-ext . cr

\ single worker, degenerate parallelism
[ 1 2 3 ] 1 1 [: 1 + :] pmap-ext . cr

\ the source array is read, never mutated
[ 1 2 3 ] dup [: 100 * :] pmap drop . cr

\ a set domain produces an image array
< 3 1 2 > [: 1 + :] pmap . cr

\ num-cores reports at least one core
num-cores 0 gt . cr

\ named word as the xt
: triple 3 * ;
[ 10 20 30 ] ' triple pmap . cr

\ pmap shortcut over a larger domain == map
1 100 range dup [: dup * 1 + :] map swap [: dup * 1 + :] pmap = . cr

\ claim 1, max contention, 500 elements == map
1 500 range dup [: sq :] map swap 8 1 [: sq :] pmap-ext = . cr

\ allocating quotation: a fresh string per element == map
1 200 range dup [: "{0}" format :] map swap [: "{0}" format :] pmap = . cr

\ interning in workers (string>symbol) == sequential interning
1 200 range dup [: "{0}" format string>symbol :] map swap 8 1 [: "{0}" format string>symbol :] pmap-ext = . cr

\ worker reuse after a fault carries no residue: region 1 faults with the side
\ stack dirty; the reused worker in region 2 must see an empty side stack, not
\ the stale value (a partial reset would leak 99 into the result).
1 1 range 1 1 [: 99 >side [ 1 2 ] 5 @i :] pmap-ext
1 1 range 1 1 [: side> :] pmap-ext . cr
